 worse, you have to protect your child first and foremost.  Not to mention, some of us have children with special needs and when we tried to go the public route, it was appauling how little help we were given.  Don't turn this around.  We pay our taxes and yet when we needed the public school system that we pay for, it let us down. I won't let my kids suffer for the mismanagement that goes on. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="694" language="en" documentId="4198" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="tigergirl857" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:39PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="10" thumbsDown="0" origId="4198" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="694"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>